# The TLS front door. Caddy provisions and renews certificates itself
# (Let's Encrypt) — with Cloudflare DNS in front, keep the proxy cloud
# ON and set SSL/TLS mode to "Full (strict)" so the orange cloud speaks
# HTTPS to this box, never plain HTTP.
#
# Two doors, one gateway: the app domain(s) serve the user shell (the
# chat), the admin domain serves the operator console. The gateway picks
# the face by the Host header Caddy forwards, so both blocks proxy to
# the same container.

# The user-facing app. OOLU_DOMAIN may list several hostnames separated
# by ", " (e.g. "app.example.com, www.app.example.com").
{$OOLU_DOMAIN} {
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy oolu:8765
}

# The operator's admin console — same gateway, the admin face.
{$OOLU_ADMIN_DOMAIN} {
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy oolu:8765
}

# The investor panel — a STATIC page, served here rather than proxied:
# the gateway answers every non-admin Host with the user shell, so this
# hostname must never reach it (and must not be listed in OOLU_DOMAIN,
# or the app shell wins). The panel calls the API cross-origin, which
# is what OOLU_ALLOW_ORIGIN admits on the oolu service. Unset,
# OOLU_INVESTORS_DOMAIN defaults (in docker-compose.prod.yml) to a
# loopback placeholder so Caddy still boots without this door.
{$OOLU_INVESTORS_DOMAIN} {
	encode gzip
	root * /srv/investors
	rewrite * /investor-panel.html
	file_server
}
